<Author>kkerr
<Content>Ideal for a city break We booked this hotel at very short notice for a weekend break in Barcelona. It was easy to reach from the airport as there is a direct rail link from the airport to the railway/metro station just across the road from the hotel costing 2Euro70. It is also ideally situated for easy access into the centre/main tourist areas (5 mins by metro day or night). No hire car needed!The check in was efficient and friendly. The reception team also had some invaluable recommendations about which sites to see and good places to dine.Our room was clean, had a separate shower and bath with twin sinks. It was airconditioned and offered the usual TV, minibar, safe (free), CD/radio and ironing board. Robes and slippers were availabe on request.The higher rooms have better views although only 3rd floor rooms had balconies.The swimming pool was more of a spa pool - small and a little disappointing although still a nice way to relax tired legs after a day exploring.Breakfast is a buffet on the top floor of the hotel - great views so try to do it once during your stay. It costs 16euros but if you book the night before at reception it will only cost 10. If you are on a budget then there is a cafe in the station or at the supermarket to the left of the hotel which serves coffee/pastries etc. We did not have dinner in the hotel prefering to eat out. Note the restaurant operates a no jeans policy in the evening.Overall we were impressed with this hotel and would recommend it. Clean, friendly, efficient and ideally located. 
