<Content>Great Hotel My husband and I booked this hotel after reading the reviews on tripadvisor. We stayed for 5 nights. Upon arrival, our bags were immediately taken from the taxi for us and this was the standard of service we received throughout the stay. Although you are not specifically in the centre of the city, Sants station is just across the road and the metro is very simple to use, air conditioned, clean and cheap, the hotel informed us of the T10 ticket. Also, you are a 10 minute walk from the 'magic fountains', which were amazing, a must see.Our room was more than adequate, very modern and clean, with a CD player, which we appreciated. The bed may have been a little too firm, but I am 6 months pregnant and find it hard to get comfortable at the moment! We ate in the lounge a few times and the menu is very good, they serve pizza, salads and other light meals. The staff there were very nice and one girl regularly asked how my baby was, which was sweet!We did not include breakfast in our booking. However, on the first morning, we opted for the breakfast, which is served on the 23rd floor. It was wonderful to see the view of the city and the range of types of breakfast on offer was vast, but the quality did not reflect the price and we opted for breakfast in the cafe in Sants station for the rest of the time, perfect if you're looking for coffee and a pastry.On our final evening, we ate in the restaurant on the 23rd floor, The menu was a fusion style, which was definitely worth trying and I thoroughly enjoyed it, though it was a little pricey, but you are paying for the view and the service was very good. My husband is a keen photographer and was itching to ask if he could come back later to take some pictures, but when we sat down, we realised that the windows were filthy! What a shame, such a lovely view and any decent picture you want to take will have dirty smears on it! However, it is still possible to take a snap to have as a memento of the view.Overal