<Author>ceadmile
<Content>Hiccups..but excellent hotel! Stayed at this hotel with my partner for a birthday treat in March. We paid 鈧?70.00 for 2 nights on Soosh.com Arrived late at night and had a few problems with the room as no-one could get the hotel safe to work. Eventually got moved at 3am!! At this stage we had to order room service and it cost 鈧?9.00 for 2 toasted sandwiches. The next morning we headed to breakfast on the 23rd floor. The view was amazing, the sun was shining and you had a panoramic view of Barcelona. The selection at breakfast was excellent. We headed out for a day sightseeing knowing that we had to move rooms again when we came back as management needed the room. On our return we were given a much larger room with a fantastic view of Font Magica. Having seen both rooms I would advise anyone booking this hotel to pay the upgrade for the rooms on the higher floors. From memory it is not very much difference financially (鈧?0 approx) but the difference is enormous. The rooms have a fantastic bathroom with walk in shower and a bath. Tiled floors run throughout and the overall feeling is modern and pristine. We actually changed our flights to return on the Sunday rather than the Saturday but as there was a football match on we had to book into a nearby hotel. Although this hotel may seem a bit further out than the usual La Rambla or more central locations it is actually very handy to get into the city from here. The Sants Estacio station is just across the road, and from behind the station you can get the Bus Turistic (鈧?8 for one day pass or 鈧?4 for a two day pass). This is a hop on hop off service and is a great way to see all the sites in a short time. After a troublesome start to the weekend I would still highly recommend this hotel. If you want to get away from the bustling La Rambla at night or prefer better quality for money I think that this is a great choice as many of the more central hotels are overpriced for the standard compared to the Torre Cataunya. Even with the problems we encountered I would stay in this hotel again. 
